    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "what_body",
      "label": "Body",
      "default": "<p>Builder is the presentation layer for the entire Fluid platform. It controls what customers and reps see on the public website — how products look, how enrollment pages are structured, what someone experiences when they land from a rep's shared link.</p><p>It is not the source of products, pricing, subscriptions, or attribution logic. Those live in other parts of the platform. Builder determines how those elements are displayed and experienced.</p><p>Think of it this way: Fluid manages what's true. Builder manages how it looks.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "what_card1_title",
      "label": "Card 1 title",
      "default": "What it controls"
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "what_card1_body",
      "label": "Card 1 body",
      "default": "How products look, enrollment page structure, landing pages, campaign experiences."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "what_card2_title",
      "label": "Card 2 title",
      "default": "What it doesn't"
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "what_card2_body",
      "label": "Card 2 body",
      "default": "Products, pricing, subscriptions, attribution logic — those live elsewhere in the platform."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Drag and Drop"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "drag_label",
      "label": "Section label",
      "default": "Visual editing"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "drag_headline",
      "label": "Headline",
      "default": "Drag, drop, publish."
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "drag_body",
      "label": "Body",
      "default": "<p>Corporate teams can build and modify pages without engineering support. Anyone who can use a standard productivity tool can use Builder. Changes are visible in real time and can be reviewed before publishing.</p><p>This isn't a simplified version of a web tool that strips away real capability. It's a web tool designed so that marketing and operations teams can use its full depth without a developer in the room.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Section Library"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "library_label",
      "label": "Section label",
      "default": "Components"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "library_headline",
      "label": "Headline",
      "default": "Start from a starting line."
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "library_body",
      "label": "Body",
      "default": "<p>Builder includes a collection of pre-built, high-converting sections — product showcases, testimonials, call-to-action blocks, enrollment flows, FAQs, media displays — that can be dropped into any page and customized.</p><p>This significantly reduces build time and ensures design quality for teams without dedicated design resources. You're not starting from a blank page. You're starting from a starting line.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Multiple Themes"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "themes_label",
      "label": "Section label",
      "default": "Version control"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "themes_headline",
      "label": "Headline",
      "default": "Multiple themes. One click to switch."
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "themes_body",
      "label": "Body",
      "default": "<p>Companies can maintain multiple complete themes within Builder simultaneously. Only one theme is live at any point. But others can be built, previewed, and held in reserve.</p><p>Switching which theme is active does not destroy the content or configuration of other themes. Seasonal redesigns, campaign launches, full site revamps — all prepared in advance, published on schedule, without risk to what's currently live.</p><p><strong>Version history and rollback:</strong> All changes in Builder are versioned. If an edit causes a problem, previous versions are accessible and restorable. Multiple layers of protection are in place to prevent unintended content loss.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "FairShare on Every Page"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "fairshare_label",
      "label": "Section label",
      "default": "Attribution"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "fairshare_headline",
      "label": "Headline",
      "default": "FairShare on every page."
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "fairshare_body",
      "label": "Body",
      "default": "<p>This is the capability most people don't expect.</p><p>FairShare attribution is applied globally through Builder. Every page built in the web editor automatically carries FairShare attribution. Every page. Not just product pages. Not just pages with a special link. Every page.</p><p>This means a rep can share the homepage. A brand story page. A product quiz. A 'Shop All' collection. A seasonal campaign landing page. And if a customer engages with it and purchases — credit follows the rep who shared it.</p><p>Corporate creates the content. Reps share it. Attribution handles itself.</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "textarea",
      "id": "fairshare_callout",
      "label": "Callout text",
      "default": "Every page. Not just product pages. Not just pages with a special link. Every page."
    },
